# Python Standards — mcp/qdrant-explorer

All root Python standards apply. MCP-specific additions:

## FastMCP pattern

- Every tool function must have a descriptive docstring — this becomes the tool description in the MCP manifest
- Tool parameters must use Pydantic models or typed primitives — no untyped `dict` parameters
- Tool names must be snake_case and self-describing

## Read-only invariant

This server ONLY uses the **read-only** Qdrant API key (`QDRANT_API_KEY_RO`).
Never accept or use a read-write key — even if passed in environment. Log a warning and refuse.

## Testing

```bash
make test     # pytest
make check    # lint + typecheck + test
```

MCP tool tests must mock `qdrant_client` — never call the live Qdrant cluster in CI.
